    "description": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "A conjunctive statement, or conjunction for short, is a statement of the \"both-and\" form. For example, \"It's both rainy and sunny\" is a conjunction. The conjuncts of a conjunction are its component statements, so the conjuncts of the example are \"It's rainy\" and \"It's sunny\".",
